1.VARIABLE

A VARIABLE is a name given to a memory location inside our computer where we can store data
EXAMPLE:
int age;
here "int" is a Keyword and "age" is a variable name
int is a integer data type
; -> semicolen is used at the end of every line which indicates the end of the statement line.
NOW Let's an example

INPUT

#include<stdio.h>
int main()
{
int age = 25;
printf("C-Porgraming");
printf(" %d",age);
return 0;
}

Notice here %d is a format specifier for integer

OUTPUT

C-Porgraming 25

2.CHANGE VALUE OF VARIABLE

#include<stdio.h>
int main()
{
int age = 25;
printf("age : %d",age);
int Newage = 27;
printf("\nNewage : %d",Newage);
return 0;
}

Notice here \n is specifier used for printing the output in the next line.

OUTPUT

age : 25
Newage : 27
